Resolution escalation/Triage

Classifies and routes work items to the correct queue, team, or workflow to minimize triage delays.

Features & Implementation

Tag: From Image; Domain: Service Assurance; Process: eTOM: Cross-Domain | ITIL: Operations Support (General); Archetype: Router/Categorizer; Autonomy: Semi-autonomous

Goals & Objectives

  • Assign work to the correct resolver group/workflow on first pass.
  • Reduce mean time to triage and misroutes.
  • Standardize categorization and priority using rules and ML signals.

Logic Synthesis100%

Process Narrative

• Read the work item context (summary, category, signals, attachments). • Classify using rules + ML features (keywords, topology, history). • Select target queue/group and recommended priority/severity. • Apply routing decision and document rationale. • Notify assignee and stakeholders; set timers/SLAs.

Security & Trust

  • Data sensitivity: Confidential (customer + network data).
  • Minimum required access only (least privilege) via RBAC; no credential sharing.
  • All writes to ITSM/CRM must be logged with before/after values and user/agent identity.
